label: NETWORK
comment: Network domain model designed to support physical and virtual networks and applications running on them. Version 5 introduces service disablement contingency plans and attacker overrides, location/network contexts for malicious access, and construction of localised infrastructure in data centres and cellular networks. Attack paths are now restricted to remain within reach of the context for the initial breach, and respect asset and capability (enabled/disabled) status while allowing for attacker overrides where control can be established.
